{"id": "c9_b_00515", "url": "https://www.zawya.com/en/economy/africa/afdb-president-calls-for-investment-in-special-agro-industrial-processing-zones-qmgdlxjd", "time": "2023-11-09", "title": "AfDB President calls for investment in Special Agro-Industrial Processing Zones", "text": "PHOTO\nMarrakech – Akinwumi Adesina, President of the African Development Bank (AfDB), called for investment in Special Agro-Industrial Processing Zones (SAPZs) at the Africa Investment Forum in Marrakech, Morocco, on Wednesday.\n“We must end the export of raw agricultural commodities,” Adesina said. “Africa must process its own cashew, cotton, coffee, tea, cocoa, cassava, fruits, and vegetables.”\nAfrica has a comparative advantage in agriculture, with 65% of the world’s uncultivated arable land. The continent’s population is expected to reach 2.5 billion by 2050, creating a huge consumption market for food.\n“The size of Africa’s food and agriculture market will be worth $1 trillion by 2030,” Adesina said. “So, think differently, and invest differently. The new millionaires and billionaires of Africa will not come from the oil and gas industry, they will be from food and agriculture.”\nAfDB provides $853m to support establishment of SAPzs\nThe AfDB has provided financing of $853m to support the establishment of SAPZs and has mobilized over $661m from other development partners.\n“The momentum of transformative change is in Africa’s favour,” Adesina said. “It’s time for Africa to be a player in global food and agricultural value chains. It’s time for Africa to fill aeroplanes and ships with processed and value-added foods and agricultural commodities.”\nThe AfDB has launched the Alliance for Special Agro-Industrial Processing Zones with founding partners Afreximbank, Islamic Development Bank, the United Nations Industrial Development Organization, and Arise Integrated Industrial Platforms.\nThe Alliance has the goal of mobilizing at least $2bn in financing and investment commitments from Alliance members and partners over the next five years.\n“I call on you, the investment community here today, to take advantage of unprecedented opportunities in Africa’s increasingly dynamic and profitable food and agricultural sector,” AfDB President said. “Invest in the Special Agro-Industrial Processing Zones (SAPZs) and be part of the new wealth of Africa.”\n© 2022 Daily News Egypt. Provided by SyndiGate Media Inc. (Syndigate.info)."}
{"id": "c9_b_00514", "url": "https://people.com/star-tracks-sunday-november-26-2023-8406601", "time": "2023-11-26", "title": "Demi Lovato Enjoys a Wintry Wonderland in Austria, Plus Tilda Swinton, Björk, Ricky Martin and More", "text": "Stars have been everywhere this week, from Demi Lovato enjoying a wintry wonderland in Austria to Tilda Swinton attending the 20th Marrakech International Film Festival in Morocco.\nHere, the best photos of celebs out and about this week. Come back tomorrow for more of the latest A-list outings!\nWinter Wonderland\nDemi Lovato poses for a picture ahead of the Top of the Mountain Opening Concert on Nov. 25 in Ischgl, Austria.\nPurple Print\nTilda Swinton attends the opening ceremony and screening of Hit Man during the 20th Marrakech International Film Festival on Nov. 24 in Marrakech, Morocco.\nSing It!\nBjörk performs on stage during a concert of her Cornucopia tour on Nov. 24 in Leipzig, Germany.\nLivin' La Vida Loca\nRicky Martin performs with dancers during a stop of The Trilogy Tour at the T-Mobile Arena on Nov. 24 in Las Vegas, Nevada.\nDazzling Diva\nJessica Chastain attends the opening ceremony and screening of Hit Man during the 20th Marrakech International Film Festival on Nov. 24 in Marrakech, Morocco.\nCheer Leader\nDolly Parton dazzles while performing during halftime of the Dallas Cowboys vs. Washington Commanders game in Texas on Thanksgiving night.\nHere to Help\nKate Middleton pays a visit to Sebby's Corner in Barnet, England, on Nov, 24, to help prepare for Christmas through her Royal Foundation Centre for Early Childhood.\nMan in Uniform\nMeanwhile, Prince William joins members of the 1st Battalion Mercian Regiment for a photo as he visits the group in Salisbury, England, on Nov. 23.\nParade Perfection\nAll wrapped up in pink and white, Brandy waves from her spot atop a float in the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade in N.Y.C.\nBring the Peace\nAlso riding through the Macy's Parade on Thanksgiving: Katharine McPhee Foster and David Foster, who share a sign with spectators.\nSparkle Motion\nPerforming just before Santa's arrival in N.Y.C., Cher brings the shimmer to the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade.\nPoster Child\nJohn Travolta spends Thanksgiving in London, attending a screening of the Disney+ original short film The Shepherd at the W London on Nov. 23.\nGrocery Games\nTaylor Lautner grabs some last-minute groceries at Erewhon in Calabasas, California, on Thanksgiving Day.\nCut It Out\nModel Jourdan Dunn has some fun with her fashion at British Vogue's 2023 Forces for Change party at The MAINE Mayfair in London on Nov. 23.\nSuit Yourself\nDan Levy keeps his cool at the Miu Miu Select event at George Club in London on Nov. 23.\nRock Royalty\nSharon Osbourne strikes a pose with Yungblud on Nov. 23 as he receives Ozzie Osbourne's The Icon Award at the inaugural Rolling Stone UK Awards at The Roundhouse in London.\nItalian Job\nMadonna continues her Celebration tour with a stop in Milan, Italy, on Nov. 23.\nCourtside Giggles\nRich Paul and Adele take date night courtside at Crypto.com Arena as the Los Angeles Lakers take on the Dallas Mavericks on Nov. 22 in L.A.\nCourtside Cool\nAndrew Garfield joins the starry crowd at the Lakers game in Los Angeles on Nov. 22.\nHollywood Outing\nWearing a belted dress and dark oversized shades, Jennifer Lopez steps out in Hollywood ahead of Thanksgiving.\nRed Carpet Smile\nRita Ora supports her husband Taika Waititi at the charity special preview for his film, Next Goal Wins, on Nov. 22 at Ham Yard Hotel in London.\nIt's Showtime\nTaika Waititi and Michael Fassbender celebrate the special charity preview of their film, Next Goal Wins, at Ham Yard Hotel in London on Nov. 22.\nMovie Star\nTom Cruise returns to the U.K. to continue shooting the next Mission Impossible film on Nov. 21.\nLending a Hand\nDenise Richards and Nick Cannon volunteer at the Los Angeles Mission's Celebrity Thanksgiving on Nov. 22 in L.A.\nStreet Style\nLooking effortlessly fabulous in a tan coat and yellow sweater, Jennifer Lawrence walks through New York City's West Village neighborhood on Nov. 22.\nCozy in the City\nWhite Lotus costars Meghann Fahy and Leo Woodall confirm romance rumors on a PDA-packed walk around N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nRain or Shine\nStaying dry underneath a clear umbrella, Ashley Park smiles at rehearsals for the 2023 Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade in N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nFlorals for Fall\nGayle King wears roses all over her dress during an appearance on Late Night with Seth Meyers in N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nThird Wheel\nParis Hilton shares a moment with Nina Dobrev and Shaun White ahead of the Las Vegas Formula 1 Grand Prix on Nov. 18.\nCouple Coordination\nColman and Raúl Domingo match in turtlenecks at a special screening of Rustin at Soho House in London on Nov. 22.\nTalk Show & Tiaras\nLate night host Seth Meyers gets goofy with Amber Ruffin and Jenny Hagel during a sketch in N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nExpecting in Color\nJessie James Decker cradles her growing baby bump in a pink suit upon arrival at NBC studios in New York City on Nov. 22.\nFamily Affair\nMick Jagger and his daughter Jade hang out at a cocktail reception before a VIP screening of I'm Still Here in London on Nov. 22.\nDecor to Adore\nWith help from Minted, celebrity interior designer Bobby Berk reveals a holiday makeover for the My Friend's Place charity in L.A. on Nov. 14.\nTeam Reunited\nKola Bokinni, David Elsendoorn, Nick Mohammed and Phil Dunster support their Ted Lasso costar Hannah Waddingham at a London celebration of her Apple TV+ special Hannah Waddingham: Home For Christmas on Nov. 22.\nBanding Together\nDawn O'Porter, Lily James, Pearl Mackie, Olivia Colman, Dermot O'Leary and Jamie Dornan don fun merch at the Nov. 22 launch of London's Choose Love pop-up shop to help refugees.\nShades On\nGigi Hadid looks chic in autumn colors as she returns to her hotel in Paris on Nov. 22.\nOpening Act\nLooking cheeky with her tongue out, Ice Spice debuts as an opener on Doja Cat's Scarlet Tour during her Miami concert on Nov. 21.\nStylish Down Under\nRegé-Jean Page wows with his wristwear on Nov. 22 at a Longines event in Sydney.\nBefore the Big Day\nBrandy bundles up in a fluffy coat at rehearsals for the upcoming Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade on Nov. 21.\nGirl Group for Good\nBLACKPINK members Lisa, Rosé, Jisoo and Jennie smile after becoming honorary Members of the Order of the British Empire thanks to their role as climate justice advocates on Nov. 22 in London.\nOn the Go\nRosie Huntington-Whiteley steps out in London on Nov. 21 looking like the picture of high fashion.\nRed Hot\nJenna Lyons pops in a red ensemble at The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon on Nov. 21.\nCenter Stage\nRita Ora belts out her hits in London during Global's Make Some Noise charity gala on Nov. 21.\nView from Outside\nSarah Paulson heads out of The View's N.Y.C. studios in a cozy beanie and coat on Nov. 22.\nStudio Days\nHalsey stands out in hot pink as she arrives to the iconic Electric Lady Studios in N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nSwimming with New Friends\nShark Tank's Daymond John visits some \"real\" sharks from Pixar's Finding Nemo at Disney World's Animal Kingdom park in Florida on Nov. 21.\nMother-Daughter Shop\nKandi Burruss (right) brings her mother Joyce Jones along to her 2023 Kandi C.A.R.E.S Foundation Thanksgiving grocery store pop-up in East Point, Georgia on Nov. 21.\nSitting Pretty\nEric McCormack settles in during his appearance on The Jennifer Hudson Show on Nov. 22.\nLaker Girl\nRooting for her home team, Becky G holds up a Lakers jersey at their game against the Utah Jazz in Los Angeles on Nov. 21.\nGetting Into Character\nTimothée Chalamet pays homage to his chocolate-making character in a purple ensemble at the Wonka premiere in Tokyo this week.\nSeeing Double\nDavid Beckham attends the U.K. Premiere of Ronnie O'Sullivan: The Edge of Everything with his son Cruz at Odeon Luxe West End on Nov. 21 in London.\nSparkle and Shine\nAmanda Seyfried is statuesque in an embellished gown at an event for Lancôme in Shanghai on Nov. 21.\nHoliday Season\nMaya Hawke, Nina Dobrev and Ashley Park keep warm as they celebrate Dior's Carousel of Dreams at Saks' holiday window and light show unveiling on Nov. 20 in N.Y.C.\nCheers!\nChase Stokes and Kelsea Ballerini stop by the Patrón Bar at the Red Bull Energy Station during F1 Las Vegas Grand Prix.\nSister, Sister\nSisters and authors Barbara Pierce Bush and Jenna Bush Hager hug it out backstage at The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon on Nov. 20 in N.Y.C.\nGenre-Blending\nKeith Urban attends the SiriusXM and Pandora present Jack Harlow inside The Chelsea soirée at The Cosmopolitan of Las Vegas on Nov. 16.\nLate Night Talking\nWanda Sykes gracefully stops by Late Night with Seth Meyers in N.Y.C. on Nov. 20.\nNew York Minute\nSister Wives' Janelle Brown and Christine Brown make an appearance at SiriusXM Studios in N.Y.C. on Nov. 21.\nDynamic Duo\nDamian and Elizabeth Hurley catch a private viewing of Mario Testino's new exhibition Gone Wild on Nov. 21 at Hamiltons Gallery in London.\nGlam Arrival\nJennifer Lawrence brings sophisticated style to the unveiling of Saks x Christian Dior's holiday display at the Saks Fifth Avenue Flagship store in N.Y.C. on Nov. 20.\nFeathery Friend\nPresident Joe Biden pardons this year's Thanksgiving turkey during a ceremony at the White House in Washington, D.C., on Nov. 20.\nRed Carpet Wonder\nLooking magical in a sheer purple ensemble, Ariana DeBose celebrates the U.K. premiere of Wish at the Odeon Luxe in London on Nov. 20.\nFast Friends\nDuring F1 weekend in Las Vegas, Michael B. Jordan kicks back with friends at XS Nightclub inside the Wynn.\nMovie Makers\nBradley Cooper and Jennifer Garner make a perfect pair at the SAG screening and Q&A for Netflix's Maestro on Nov. 18 in Los Angeles.\nPooch Pal\nJoe Manganiello looks especially buff after a gym session while carrying his tiny dog on Nov. 19 in L.A.\nStriking a Pose\nDirector Taika Waititi brings the drama at the Berlin premiere of his new film Next Goal Wins on Nov. 20.\nIndustry Talk\nSterling K. Brown speaks at the SAG-AFTRA Foundation Robin Williams Center during a conversation about his film American Fiction on Nov. 20 in N.Y.C.\nOn Ice\nPrince Harry drops the puck for Quinn Hughes of the Vancouver Canucks and Tomas Hertl of the San Jose Sharks prior to their game at Rogers Arena in Vancouver on Nov. 20.\nGolden State Star\nEllie Goulding hits a high note during her performance with the San Francisco Symphony at the Louise M. Davies Symphony Hall on Nov. 20.\nCostars & Companions\nPaul Mescal and Andrew Scott pose together at an L.A. screening of All of Us Strangers in L.A.\nWinning Moment\nKarla Souza looks elated to hold her award at the 1st International Emmy Awards in New York City on Nov. 20.\nWelcome Party\nPrince William and Kate Middleton help welcome Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol and First Lady Kim Keon Hee in London on Nov. 21.\nAcross the Pond\nCorey Hawkins, Taraji P. Henson, Danielle Brooks, Fantasia Barrino and Colman Domingo line up in style at a photo call for The Color Purple on Nov. 21 in London.\nOut & About\nChris Pratt and Katherine Schwarzenegger step out in warm attire for lunch in L.A. on Nov. 20.\n'Tis the Season\nKate Middleton sports a cozy turtleneck sweater as she gears up for the upcoming Westminster Abbey special Christmas carol service.\nCoupled Up\nWith a coffee in hand, Jack Antonoff steps out in New York City with his wife, Margaret Qualley, on Nov. 19.\nSpecial Night\nTaraji P. Henson stuns in a pink ensemble at a VIP screening for The Color Purple at the Regent Street Cinema in London on Nov. 20."}
