{"id": "c9_b_00106", "url": "https://northafricapost.com/73041-moroccos-king-says-will-continue-to-work-with-spains-pedro-sanchez-for-stronger-strategic-partnership.html", "time": "2026-05-14", "title": "Morocco's King says will continue to work with Spain's Pedro Sanchez for stronger strategic partnership", "text": "King Mohammed VI has voiced his firm determination to continue working with Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez to strengthen further the strategic partnership adopted by the two countries on the basis of \"neighborliness, mutual trust, and permanent and constructive dialogue.\"\nIn a congratulatory message sent to Mr. Sanchez after he won a new term as PM following the support of the majority of lawmakers, ending a four-month political deadlock, the Moroccan Sovereign wished him success in achieving the aspirations of the friendly Spanish people to greater progress and prosperity.\nThe Monarch also reiterated his strong determination to continue working for the consolidation of relations of friendship and advancing cooperation ties between the two countries.\nKing Mohammed V praised the commitment of the two neighboring countries to coordinate stands on various regional and international issues of common interest in line with their centuries-old civilizational & cultural heritage shared by the two friendly peoples, contributing to the preservation of peace, stability and prosperity in the Euro-Mediterranean region.\nUnder Sanchez administration, Spain has clearly backed in 2022 Morocco's autonomy plan as the only political solution to the Sahara issue."}
{"id": "c9_b_00099", "url": "https://www.africa-newsroom.com/press/morocco-his-majesty-the-king-congratulates-mauritanian-president-on-independence-day?lang=en", "time": "2023-11-28", "title": "Morocco: His Majesty The King Congratulates Mauritanian President on Independence Day", "text": "Morocco: His Majesty The King Congratulates Mauritanian President on Independence Day\nThe Sovereign expresses on His behalf and that of the Moroccan people His warmest congratulations to Ould Cheikh El Ghazouani and His best wishes for further progress and prosperity to the Mauritanian people\nHis Majesty the King praises the fraternal ties uniting the Kingdom of Morocco and the Islamic Republic of Mauritania\nHM King Mohammed VI sent a message of congratulations to His Excellency President of the Islamic Republic of Mauritania, Mohamed Ould Cheikh El Ghazouani, on the occasion of his country's Independence Day.\nIn this message, the Sovereign expresses on His behalf and that of the Moroccan people His warmest congratulations to Ould Cheikh El Ghazouani and His best wishes for further progress and prosperity to the Mauritanian people.\nOn this occasion, His Majesty the King praises the fraternal ties uniting the Kingdom of Morocco and the Islamic Republic of Mauritania, reaffirming His strong determination to continue working with the Mauritanian Head of State to strengthen the solid, age-old relations between the two countries, so as to raise them to the level of strategic cooperation and the shared aspirations of the two peoples.\nDistributed by APO Group on behalf of Kingdom of Morocco - Ministry of Foreign Affairs, African Cooperation and Moroccan Expatriates."}
{"id": "c9_b_00145", "url": "https://northafricapost.com/73953-russian-arab-ministers-laud-moroccos-king-role-in-defending-jerusalem.html", "time": "2026-05-14", "title": "Russian-Arab ministers laud Morocco's King role in defending Jerusalem", "text": "The Russian-Arab Cooperation Forum, held in Marrakech at the foreign ministers' level, welcomed the key role played by King Mohammed VI, Chairman of Al Quds committee, in safeguarding the city of Jerusalem and supporting its people.\nThe forum \"supports the role of the presidency of the Jerusalem Committee and its efforts to counter the practices of the occupying authorities in the Holy City, and support the resilience of Jerusalem and Jerusalemites through the programs and projects of Bayt Mal Al-Quds Al-Sharif Agency,\" reads the joint statement.\nThe Russian and Arab ministers also lauded Morocco's leadership and efforts to settle a set of Arab issues, including the crisis in Libya. The final declaration \"emphasizes the principle of Libyan ownership of the political process, and commit to the Libyan Political Agreement signed in Skhirat in 2015.\nRegarding Morocco's role in countering terrorism, the Russian-Arab Cooperation Forum welcomed the hosting of the Kingdom of the 93rd session of the General Assembly of the International Criminal Police Organization (Interpol) in Marrakech in 2025, as well as the hosting of the United Nations Office of Counter-Terrorism.\nIt also valued the kingdom's role and efforts during the chairmanship of the Global Counter-Terrorism Forum (2021-2023).\nIn addition, the Forum welcomed the outcomes of the annual meetings of the World bank Group and the International Monetary Fund, which were held in Marrakech on October 9-15, 2023, especially those related to financing climate activities and achieving Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).\nFinally, the Arab and Russian Foreign ministers welcomed the choice of the Kingdom of Morocco to host the 2030 Football World Cup."}
